    {
      "id": "observability-signal-watch",
      "kind": "agent",
      "name": "Observability Signal Watch",
      "version": "1.2.3",
      "status": "verified",
      "text": "Name: Observability Signal Watch\nDescription: Analyzes logs, alerts, and service metrics to detect noisy monitors, missing coverage, and weak incident signals.\nOrganization: SEL-Core\nStatus: verified\nVersion: 1.2.3\nTechnologies: Prometheus, Grafana, OpenTelemetry\nPrimary specialization: observability_engineering\nDomain specific: Alert Quality, Telemetry Coverage, Incident Detection\nTasks: Audit Alert Rules - Flags duplicate alerts, weak thresholds, and noisy paging conditions.; Review Telemetry Coverage - Checks whether critical paths expose enough logs, metrics, and traces for debugging.\nDocumentation: https://github.com/sel/observability/blob/main/signal-watch/README.md https://github.com/sel/observability/blob/main/signal-watch/README.md#usage v1.2.3 improves alert grouping and telemetry gap analysis",
